x4freetext: Low  Limit  of  the  Uncertainty  of  Absolute
Calibration of Used Spectrometer.
High Limit of the Uncertainty of Absolute
Calibration of Used Spectrometer.
This Information has Been Extracted by Compiler from
Irradiation Time was 11 Minutes.
. The Measurments were Began After 15 Minutes
Of  End  of Irradiation, Approximately. 34 Measurements
Have Been Executed During to 18 Hours.  Each Measurment
Was from 10 to 60 Minutes.  Additional Measurement  has
Been Executed After 1 Day, 25 Days and Half Year.
The  Stack  has  Contained  Aluminium  and Lead
Foils.  All Foils have Diameter 30 mm.  Thicknesse  was
0.1  mm  of  Lead.   All  Targets  in  this  Stack were
Surrounded by Additional  Identical  Foils  to  Exclude
Activity Loss.
-By Compiler- Any Information About Energy
Degradation in Used Stack is Absent.
